name: Sunday Brunch
description: Join us for brunch in the heart of Pike Place Market! Chef Eric is hosting this hybrid hands-on and demonstration class to teach how to make an unforgettable meal using fresh ingredients from our Northwest cuisine. This class begins with a tour where you will see the market through a chef's eyes while selecting delicious, fresh produce together. You'll then settle into the stunning Atrium kitchen as the cooking begins in this 2.5 hour class. Have a drink and help yourself to snacks from our local vendors, then roll up your sleeves as the Eric teaches you how to make colorful seasonal frittata and fluffy dutch baby pancakes. You’ll learn the details that make the dish, such as balancing flavors in the different courses, and create two unique pancake sauces. This experience includes the a market tour, discounts on our market vendors, drinks, snacks and a delicious brunch.

itemListElement.name: Mt. Rainier National Park Small Group Tour from Seattle with Gourmet Lunch

name: Mt. Rainier National Park Small Group Tour from Seattle with Gourmet Lunch
description:
With a charming naturalist as your companion, stretch your legs through an old growth forest surrounded by 800-year old trees towering above you. Feel the cool mist blowing off glacier fed waterfalls carving through an ancient canyon. Refuel your energy with a chef-prepared picnic in the wilderness. Encounter the largest glaciers in the lower 48 as you stroll through alpine meadows above 5,000' while looking for wildlife. With your guide's help, spot mountaineers heading for the summit--a human drama unfolding before your eyes.

- Learn Mt. Rainier’s natural history on 4-6 guided nature walks. 
- Leave the crowds behind with a small group of 10 guests or less. 
- Explore the best photo spots for any season or weather. 
- A knowledgeable, certified guide at your side to inform and entertain.

review.name: Mt. Ranier BEST TOUR ever!!!
review.reviewBody: Michael of Nature Nuts was the absolute BEST! The tour to Mt. Ranier was by far the greatest tour of our trip to Seattle and the Pacific Northwest.  We lucked out with a gorgeous day and the mountain top was visible, something Michael informed us doesn't happen too often. The gourmet lunch was amazing and the tour was chock full of activity and time to rest and enjoy the breathtaking views. The views were indescribable - such beauty, it was like we were in a different country. Michael had every detail handled and was such a gracious host. Thank you for the incredible experience Michael. This was the last tour of our visit to Seattle and we definitely saved the best for last.

review.name: Mt. Rainier Adventure & Experience
review.reviewBody: So many good things to say about this experience. Where do I start? Maybe the views. They were fantastic! The views though would not not been possible if our tour guide Michael did not do his weather homework before hand. With the ever changing weather patterns of Mt Rainier, especially late in the season, it was very important to do that. We started at the top and worked our way down the mountain. By time we started our journey back down the mountain and back to the city, the top of the mountain was covered in clouds. If we would have done the opposite, we would have been in clouds and would never have seen the views or gotten the pictures we did . Thank you Michael for taking the time to make our experience the best it could be, and for being such an awesome and descriptive tour guide you are. Make sure you include this trip the next time you are in Seattle!

review.name: BEST TOUR EVER!
review.reviewBody: This tour with Michael of Nature Nuts was by far my very best Seattle area experience!!! WHY? (1) MT Rainier is incredible (2) It was a gorgeous day! (3) Michael is the best tour guide I have had ANYWHERE - IN THE WORLD! Michael is experienced, organized, and great at creating a comradery among the guests. So, (4) The best tour group ever! We went on a beautiful (slightly strenuous – uphill) hike to (5) the most incredible views! (6) We had multiple diverse stops/treks to different mountain views, Reflection Lake and an old growth forest. (7) We never had to worry about anything – it is a total turn-key experience – never a worry about any of your needs.  Also, the best actual gourmet lunch. When you have a choice/chance to use Nature Nuts – you should! Thank you, thank you, thank you Michael!!!

review.name: Mt.Rainier day trip
review.reviewBody:
What an AMAZING trip! ( 9/19/21)
Our guide Michael was above and beyond! Even though there was rain in the forecast we got up to Sunrise before the weather even started and ended up with an amazing hike! We went down the the white river, the old forest and even hiked to some waterfalls! It was an amazing and memorable trip and we can’t wait to come back and do another trip with you guys!!!

review.name: Unique experience - highly recommended
review.reviewBody:
We joined the Mt. Rainier tour as our pre-cruise excursion with Michael just a week ago.  We booked the tour few months ahead as advanced planning.  Michael was very responsive and patient to address our concerns.  About a week prior to the adventure, he provided updates and preparation details which gave us peace of mind.

Michael is very professional and shares with us his in-depth knowledge about the National Park.  Despite the not-so-cooperative weather (very wet and foggy), it was a nice hike.  Michael took us to different areas of the parks with his very well-maintained van.  We covered mountain peak, forest, waterfalls and glacier river.  It was a very unique experience.   We also had plenty of time to take photos and appreciate the scenery.  But, we must admit that we were exhausted after a full day event.

The lunch was included in the tour and it was delicious with various options of protein.  Michael also prepared snacks and hot drinks for us.  The chocolate cookies made by his wife were the best.  
We highly recommend this tour to anyone who love hiking and want to explore Mt. Rainier National Park.

review.name: Must do when in Seattle
review.reviewBody: I had a great time on this tour, Michael our tour guide, was great and was very knowledgeable about the mountain. He took us to all the great spots, i highly recommend this tour. I went sept 15, great time to go, at this time there are no mosquitos which is well worth it to me. Although the wild flowers are mostly dead at this time but i personally prefer 0 mosquitos.

review.name: Outstanding day trip from Seattle!
review.reviewBody: My wife and I decided to spend a couple of extra days in Seattle after an Alaskan Cruise.  The weather at Mt. Rainier turned out to be great and Michael did a excellent job as our guide.  We were able to experience multiple locations in the National Park and I know that we saw a lot more than we would have on our own.  I highly recommend Nature Nuts for your Seattle area excursions!

review.name: Awesome family day trip
review.reviewBody: Micheal was very knowledgeable, on time, very attentive to our needs and got in touch with us the day before to tell us what to expect and how to prepare .  The morning of, he kept us informed of his arrival time.  The vehicle was very nice and clean!  Oh,and the food was excellent!  We do a trip with Nature Nuts again for sure!

review.name: Excellent Day with Nature Nuts
review.reviewBody: Simply the best guided tour on which I have ever been. Michael's attention to detail made the trip the highlight of our entire vacation. His knowledge and enthusiasm for what he does really shines through and makes the experience so memorable. He can make even the shyest guest feel comfortable and excited about what they are seeing. Michael knew all the best spots to stop at on our tour, the hidden gems and roads less travelled. He kept the van stocked with goodies and really took great care of his guests. Another huge plus was Micheals driving skills. As someone who is prone to motion sickness I can assure you Michael drives incredibly well, no sudden jerks or slamming on brakes or "speeding up just to slow down". Lunch was awesome, too. I just cant say enough about this tour experience, you do NOT want to miss an opportunity to tour with Nature Nuts.

review.name: Great excursion
review.reviewBody: Great tour of Mount Rainier with a knowledgeable, funny, and a great tour guide! We hiked, saw Marmots, Elk, ate delicious food, learned a lot about Mount Rainier and the forest. Michael even helped with logistical tips for the rest of my vacation! Highly recommend this group tour!

itemListElement.name: San Juan Islands Seaplane Flight & Hiking Adventure Tour from Seattle

name: San Juan Islands Seaplane Flight & Hiking Adventure Tour from Seattle
description:
On this full-day air and land adventure, soar over Seattle and Puget Sound in a private seaplane to the wild outer San Juan Islands. Your guide will lead you on a 1-1.5-hour excursion over forested trails, along wild beaches above rugged cliffs that ring the island. 

During the hike, you’ll learn about the area's natural history and your guide will show you the best photo spots. As we go, we’ll keep an eye out for wildlife. We frequently spot bald eagles, harbor seals, sea lions, and harbor porpoises. 
Enjoy a delicious picnic and drinks before flying back to Seattle for flyby of the waterfront and the Space Needle. 

-Escape to wild outer San Juan Islands on a 1 hour 40 minutes round-trip seaplane flight.
-Land at a beach and explore the island on a guided naturalist hike. 
-Indulge in a delicious chef-prepared picnic lunch amidst the island’s beauty.
-Fly by the Seattle waterfront, Lake Union, and the Space Needle.

review.name: Great experience!
review.reviewBody: This was an amazing experience from start to finish. Our guide, Michael was knowledgeable and professional. He was able to accommodate a schedule change when our original date was derailed by a heatwave. The flight was incredible & comfortable, even for a nervous flyer like myself. The scenery en route was fantastic, & there was a lovely hike on the island with gorgeous views. Lunch on the beach was very tasty. Thanks to Michael & our pilot, Jim, from Friday Harbor Seaplanes, for an anniversary to remember!

review.name: Fun and original adventure
review.reviewBody: Great trip. Had a problem with aircraft alternator during pre-flight check, but Michael was able to secure an alternate in less than an hour. The trip was fantastic (got good weather!), got to experience water take off and landing, then a nice 2 hr hike on a uninhabited island. Bonus: a birder came with us and pointed out some interesting fowl. Ended with a nice lunch, provided by Michael, on a bluff overlooking our seaplane in the cove.

review.name: Great custom trip for small group
review.reviewBody: Michael organized a perfect day for three people where we did the San Juan Islands Seaplane hiking tour (where we lucked out and saw whales from the air), and then a 90 minute helicopter tour towards Mt. Rainier and then exploring the mountains, Snoqualmie Falls, and back over the city.  Lunch was better than I was expecting, and Michael did a great job of offering me vegan food with meat for my friends.

name: Afternoon 3-Hour Seattle City Tour
description: Small group tours of Seattle. Space Needle, Pike Place Market, and all major attractions, highlights, and picture postcard photo-ops on a three hour tour in comfortable motor coaches with tours of never more than 14 guests. Fun, entertaining, and informative guides provide local flavor with personal anecdotes and historical nuggets only a local could know.

review.name: Loved this tour!
review.reviewBody: Dave (Elvis!) was awesome! He gave a detailed and entertaining tour that truly encompassed all that Seattle has to offer. I would recommend this tour to anyone looking to explore the city.

review.name: Excellent Seattle History Tour with James Grindle
review.reviewBody: James Grindle was extremely knowledgeable about Seattle's history, and this was truly a fun, educational tour!  He was friendly, flexible and an overall awesome tour guide...one of the best we have ever had!

review.name: worth the time and money
review.reviewBody:
Very interesting, the guide, James, was a wealth of information!
Kept the tour moving, had many interesting tidbits.
I would take the, tour again, just to try to injest  all the historical facts and stories.

review.name: Poor company
review.reviewBody: Lelia, our guide, was great. The company is not.  The communication was poor for our pickup and an hour of our time was wasted. I would not recommend.

review.name: Great city tour!
review.reviewBody: DC was an informative and fun guide! He taught us so much about the history of the city. All of the landmarks we saw were incredible. We especially loved the market and the locks and fish ladder. Overall this was an excellent experience, and we would recommend it to anyone visiting Seattle!

review.name: A history class was well worth the time!
review.reviewBody: Excellent tour with excellent information! Everyone should do this! I learned so much, I feel like I received, a full circle of Seattle!

review.name: Perfect Pre-Cruise Excursion!
review.reviewBody: Our party of 5 loved this tour!  What a great overview of Seattle when you're limited on time!  Our guide "Lucky" was a wealth of information and made the whole afternoon fun!  We had a great time!!! Thank you Lucky!!!

review.name: This tour was excellent!
review.reviewBody: Very informative and friendly host, great transport, excellent coverage of Seattle area. Highly recommend.

review.name: Pre Cruise your if Seattle
review.reviewBody: We had Dave(Elvis) as our guide & he was amazing, he barely paused for breath for the entire tour & just gave us so much good & useful information in such a light funny way. The entire journey flew in & was thoroughly enjoyed by everyone. Thanks Elvis for an amazing afternoon

review.name: Good Way to See Most of Seattle
review.reviewBody:
Overall- Average tour.  Good way to get an overview of Seattle.  I booked the tour directly through the company.  Good thing because I got a AAA discount which I would not have gotten had I booked through Viatour (Trip Advisor.) 
We met at Wells Fargo bank and there were only four of us total.  (Nice) My mom and I and two ladies from Germany.  Our tour guide was a 22 year Navy veteran and former Uber driver. I think his name was Dave. 

The Pros: He was pretty knowledgable about the area and gave us a lot of history about Chief Seattle and Captain Vancouver.  
Told us about rough ocean conditions in the Pacific Northwest and the dangers of being a fisherman. 
Talked throughout the tour giving us good historical info. 
We went to most of the areas stated on the trip.
They provided bottled water.

Cons:
He was kind of a know it all.  When his microphone was picking up annoying interference from his cell phone he refused to believe me.  He kind of argued with me and after telling him about having a degree in TV Broadcasting and working for a TV station for 20 years and THAT IS the cause of the exact sound his mic was making he countered with the fact that he had 20 years in electronics.  SO?  What does that have to do with anything. He finally turned his cell phone off and that ended the interference.  (Told ya!) 
When streets were closed he was very annoyed.  Ok, well stuff happens. Deal with it.  
The van was very hot after stops.  He could have kept it on instead of us waiting several minutes for it to cool down.  
Ballard Locks- Rushed through.  My mom and the two German ladies were all over the age of 65.  Why make them practically run up and down the hill?  Come on. 
(oh, and when I told him about going to China and going through the locks on the Yangtze River (3rd longest in the world) and that it took several hours- he was like, ALL locks work the same and they only take a few minutes!  I was like, well ours took hours.  He just dismissed me.  (Looked it up online- it takes approximately FOUR hours!)  He made me feel like I was some kind of dumb*ss and didn't know what I was talking about. (When it was actually HE that didn't.)
Sometimes when I asked a question he seemed annoyed. 
Fremont Neighborhood- We didn't even go.  The Famous Freemont troll?  We didn't even see it.
He drove up to Kerry park so we could take a picture of Seattle. After that he asked if we wanted to be dropped off anywhere.  I said, Well, aren't you supposed to take us to the Space Needle?  He said, yes- and I said, ok, well drop us off there.  Not sure if he would have gone past it had I not said anything.  
Overall the trip was fine.  Maybe he needs a new job and doesn't like that he was once a decorated Officer and now had to deal with measly civilians.  Who knows?  I was in the military too.  (USAF)

Book directly through the company to save some money.  
Expect to rush through locks.  Be prepared for attitude. Good tour that is comparable to the other tour companies.  I think this one is a little cheaper that Northwest.  That is why I chose it.

name: Patagōn
description: Welcome to Patagon, where classic American flavors meet a relaxed atmosphere. Start your day right with our delicious brunch menu, served daily from 7 AM to 2 PM, featuring everything from fluffy French toast and savory benedicts to freshly brewed coffee. Then, unwind during our popular happy hour from 2 PM to 5 PM, with great drink specials and light bites. As evening falls, enjoy our selection of seafood, juicy steaks, and timeless American favorites, prepared with the finest ingredients. Whether you're here for brunch, happy hour, or a hearty dinner, we offer an inviting space to gather with friends and family and savor the best of American cuisine.

name: Trad Climbing Course
description: This two-day course introduces students to traditional (trad) climbing on routes that follow cracks. Students will learn how to select equipment, place and remove protection, build simple trad anchors, and climb cracks and other natural features. These skills prepare students to climb at rock climbing destinations and in the mountains throughout the United States. Our course utilizes phenomenal learning environments such as the Index Town Walls of Washington where students find an abundance of traditional climbs of all difficulties. If students are interested in learning how to lead trad routes this course can be combined with our Trad Lead Climbing Course. Previous climbing experience is required for this course with outdoor climbing experience preferred. This can be gained on our Intro to Outdoor Rock Climbing trip.

review.name: Top Notch Experience
review.reviewBody:
My friend and I wanted to home our traditional climbing experience went to Miyar to help us. They hooked us up with Chloé, who was super knowledgeable, able to communicate ideas clearly, and was always encouraging us. She took the time to walk us through fundamentals as well as introduce more advanced topics as we progressed. Chloé is a 5 star guide and I hope to work with her in the future.

Working with Miyar to schedule the weekend was easy. I left a voicemail and Sandeep called me to set up the time that would work best. They were responsive and provided all the necessary information to make our weekend a success. I felt like we were in very good hands the whole time.

review.name: Super accomodating, flexible, knowledgable and insightful instructor
review.reviewBody:
I had two great days learning about traditional climbing. The instructor Glen is super knowledgable and insightful about everything from gear, protection to how to transition on multipitch belays, and everything in between. Glen was super flexible and accommodating to our hours and lodging preferences. His explanations were very clear and he made to go at a pace that you can follow, and allows for a lot of hands on practice. He was super patient and answered all of our questions with great insight. Our outing did involve a bit of scrambling on 4th class terrain, rappeling and even following him on easy trad multipitch that he led. In all occassions, he was super conscious of safety and made it feel safe by explaining clearly what he was doing and how he was keeping us protected. 
He also provided us with great conversation, and he was super insightful about everything outdoors. We also had tons of laughs and just a good time in general. All in all, had a great experience! Highly recommended for those that want to learn about trad climbing and get a solid understanding of the fundamentals.

itemListElement.name: Full-Day Guided Mount Rainier Tour from Seattle with Transport

name: Full-Day Guided Mount Rainier Tour from Seattle with Transport
description:
Private tour.

Visit Mount Rainier National Park on this full-day tour. See waterfalls, old-growth forests, flowering meadows, and wildlife in their natural habitat. This experience on Mount Rainier makes your expected stops — but also ventures off the beaten path, with fantastic views and vistas, waterfalls, and park grounds. This tour travels all the way around Mount Rainier, and the different landscapes are fantastic. Four stops for trail walks and/or waterfalls are included.

review.name: Wonderful Adventure
review.reviewBody: We had a wonderful time on our adventure.  The vehicle was comfortable and Janet was an excellent, informative, funny with a great personality.  She tailored the trip to our interests and was knowledgeable.  Highly recommend!

review.name: Fact filled Mt Ranier trip
review.reviewBody: Cheryl's tour to Mt Ranier was perfect for us. She was very informative, with a good mix of historical,  geological, and local facts as we made our way to Mt Ranier.  She customized our trip to include the most scenic areas so my photographer husband could really take in the majestic beauty of Mt Ranier.  NIce for couples and small groups. We were at the end of the seasons, so options for lunch were rather limited. Might be could to pack cooler with something from the market before heading out.

review.name: My Rainier Day Trip
review.reviewBody: Wonderful experience. Scenery is breathtaking, Driver/guide, Ron, was excellent - very knowledgeable, courteous and accommodating. We learned quite a lot about the park and it’s eco system from Ron. One of the highlights of our trip. Highly recommended!

itemListElement.name: Deception Pass Bridge Island Tour from Seattle

name: Deception Pass Bridge Island Tour from Seattle
description:
Private Experience only for you
We are different. We love our customers and our Pacific Northwest
Stop and walk across Deception Pass Bridge
Collect rocks at the beach, a local favorite past time
Visit historic Coupeville and the first pier on Puget Sound
Ferry ride to get back to the mainland

review.name: Best way to experience the area !
review.reviewBody: Great tour and wonderful way to experience outside of the city . We were picked up at our hotel by Cheryl and driven safely to experience breathtaking water views, historical places like Ft Casey , beaches , friendly tavern for lunch and local shopping , explore a rhododendron garden then ferry ride back followed by busy ride back to Seattle . Along the way lots of history and facts about the area was given along with some laughs. Cheryl is a lovely experienced guide. Worth every dollar!

review.name: Whidbey Island day trip
review.reviewBody: Cheryl’s tour was the highlight of my Seattle trip. I was picked up directly from my hotel.  She was extremely knowledgeable about Whidbey Island and shared many interesting facts. I could tell that she catered to my interests and adjusted the tour accordingly. At one point we spotted a bald eagle directly about the vehicle. I jokingly asked her where the button was that she pushed to release the Eagle. I truly had a wonderful tour.

review.name: Whidbey Island Tour
review.reviewBody: The tour was great.  I really enjoyed the view from Deceptions pass. You also must try the salmon jerky.

review.name: Awesome
review.reviewBody: Didn’t spend long here but did witness an amazing sunset. Interesting stories about the place. Bust bridge for traffic.

review.name: Deception Pass on Whidbey Island so beautiful!
review.reviewBody: This is the second time I have been to Deception Pass on Whidbey Island with Cheryl's Northwest Tours. The first time was for the annual (and delicious) Mussel Festival. I enjoyed that trip so much that I decided to go on the Deception Pass Bridge Island tour and I was not disappointed. This tour company really makes you feel important. They only use SUV size vehicles that limit the number of people who can take the tour at the same time. It makes for such a personal and specialized outing and it's great to be able to talk to the tour guide one-on-one without a bus full of people to contend with. Thanks for another great day and all of the beautiful scenery that we enjoyed together. I can't say enough good things about this tour company and the great people who work there. I will be back!

review.name: Private Day Trip -- Seattle to Whidbey Island and Back
review.reviewBody:
After being told by our travel agent that no private tours to Whidbey Island were available, I found Cheryl on Trip Advisor.  I contacted her, explained what we wanted to do (which included a drive down the street in Mount Vernon where my parents lived in 1943), plus stops in Oak Harbor at the PBY Museum and near the Naval Air Station where my dad was based during WWII as a PBY pilot, and she said no problem.

Cheryl was very accomodating of all of our  requests.  She also was very knowledgable of the Puget Sound area and its history and geography.  We walked the bridge at Deception Pass and toured the park.  She took us to a great waterfront spot for lunch in Coupeville.  Our day concluded with a ride back to the mainland on the Whidbey Island ferry.

Our vehicle was clean and comfortable, and Cheryl was very personable.  She picked us off and dropped us off at our downtown Seattle hotel.  If you want a personalized tour of the Northwest,    contact her!  I am glad we did!!

itemListElement.name: General Admission to Living Computers Museum and Labs

name: General Admission to Living Computers Museum and Labs
description: Say hello to a world of working computers! From vintage systems to the latest digital tools, discover technology at your fingertips inside Living Computers: Museum + Labs. With daily tours and hands-on exhibits, we’re one of Seattle’s top-rated attractions you won’t want to miss. Come in. Geek out.

review.name: Unique and hands-on
review.reviewBody: Very unique museum with exhibits covering 1970s onwards. Plenty of hands-on activities. Good rainy day choice for kids of all ages. A bit expensive; had to get an annual membership to make the family visit cheaper.

review.name: Great for kids of all ages
review.reviewBody: Do NOT miss this amazing museum.  It's hands-on for a huge collection of older computers plus a large number of mainframes and older relics.  Great docents give tours and know their stuff!

review.name: It takes me back!
review.reviewBody: I started programming computers in 1969 and progressed thru the years from working with mainframes and personal computer towers to laptops. So, this museum took me back to my youth. I have over the years with a number of the computers they have in the museum. It's amazing to look at a core memory page or a 'cake pan' disk drive and realize what little data they store compared to the simplest, smallest smartphone available today.

review.name: Very interactive and nostalgic
review.reviewBody: Fascinating museum taking you back to early computing and up to the modern day. If you have kids who won't get off computers this might convince them to give museums a try! Lots of terminals from different eras to try simple commands and programming on. Some modern robotics and gadgets to play with too. Some of the terminals weren't working but there were staff on hand who we could have asked for help. We were there a couple of hours. Note that the cafe area is a place you can eat sandwiches rather than a cafe serving food.

review.name: Wonderful museum
review.reviewBody: If you are at all interested in the history of computing, this is a must-see. All sorts of equipment, much of which is running and you can try for yourself!

itemListElement.name: Area Tours, Rental Tours, International and Concierge Settling In Services

name: Area Tours, Rental Tours, International and Concierge Settling In Services
description: Sprout provides high touch, customized relocation services to individuals in the Pacific NW. We are a unique business, because we specialize on the settling in process with specialized skills and training to help enhance the efficiency of a relocation, easing the jolt of a big move. Our team has backgrounds in HR, Mobility and personal relocated both Nationally and Internationally, as well as grown up and spent their lives in the greater Seattle Area. Each tour specialist is hand matched based upon the client's experiences and interests. Going on 8 years and helping 1000s of clients, let us help show you all that Washington has to offer!

name: Private Seattle Cocktail Tour
description:
Learn about the history of the neighborhood , walk among some great outdoor street art, enjoy some excellent craft cocktails and taste spirits that are made right here in the area! Throughout our walking tour, we’ll be passing by some interesting landmarks in Fremont, including a historic canal, modern-day tech headquarters, some truly bizarre outdoor art, and the famous Fremont Troll.
Highlights
- Enjoy a taste of some locally made spirits - made right here in the Pacific Northwest
- Discover some funky art throughout the Fremont neighbourhood
- Learn the stories behind the cocktails and their ingredients
- Hear about Seattle's Prohibition past and its modern-day drinking scene
- This tour is carbon neutral, operated by a B Corp certified company committed to using travel as a force for good.

review.name: Highly Recommend
review.reviewBody:
Lee was excellent! He’s an incredible 
wealth of knowledge when it comes to cocktails and he’s such a warm and nice guy. I enjoyed the bars we visited in Fremont. 10/10 would recommend.

review.name: Best way to learn, with drinks!
review.reviewBody: Had a wonderful time with Lee walking around Fremont, Seattle. The cocktails and recommendations were amazing and he was so knowledgeable! We had so much fun, and still managed to learn a thing or two along the way. I would absolutely recommend this tour, and especially Lee. Friendly, funny and fun!

review.name: Cocktail Crawl
review.reviewBody: We stayed in Fremont and wanted to get familiar with the area.  Lee was good at communicating and knowledgeable about the city history and the cocktails we tasted.  He is a good guide and made it quite enjoyable

review.name: Fantastic Fremont cocktail tour
review.reviewBody: Great tour! Delicious cocktails, interesting history of Fremont, and our Guide (Lee) was fantastic! I loved each of the 3 stops and we decided to stay and have dinner at the last stop…highly (not hi-lee 😆) recommend this tour!

review.name: Excellent cocktail tour
review.reviewBody: I had a great time learning about great bars in Fremont! I also enjoyed hearing about different cocktails and the history of Prohibition. The guide was very friendly and knowledgeable regarding bars in the Seattle area/good cocktails to order.

review.name: AWESOME TIME
review.reviewBody: GREAT TOUR! HIGHLY RECOMMENDED! I HAD SO MUCH FUN EXPLORING THE DIFFERENT BARS AROUND SEATTLE AND ENJOYING THE DIFFERENT DRINKS.

review.name: Boozy Stroll
review.reviewBody: Had a lot of fun learning about the history of cocktails in the city and drinking them along the way!

review.name: Amazing tour in Seattle
review.reviewBody: One of the best tours I have ever experienced! Lee was great! He knew so much about cocktails, about Fremont and about Seattle. We had an awesome time and will be back to Fremont and recommend Lee to all our friends.

review.name: One of the better Seattle tours out there!
review.reviewBody:
Lee was amazing!! Very knowledgeable about cocktails, Fremont and Seattle.
We left the tour with a strong desire to go back there and explore all the other places he recommended along the way.

review.name: Lee is the bee's knees (the good version of the saying)
review.reviewBody: The walking tour with Lee was such a great way to experience a bit of Seattle I wouldn't normally see. I was in town for a conference and tagged along with my colleague and her son and I'm so glad I did. Not only were the drinks great, but Lee was engaging and knowledgeable without being snobby. He rolled with the punches (we're a rowdy trio) and made the experience really fun. Ypu can tell he likes being a guide and has respect for the craft. Highly recommend if you're in the Seattle area!
